h3. Summary

Adobe Captivate presentations with table of contents are not reproduced by the Multimedia Macro in Confluence. Presentations without TOC are reproduced correctly with no issues. 
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Insert the presentation with table of contents to the page (drag and drop or use the insert menu and add the Multimedia Macro);
 # Save the page and it reloads;
 # Presentation is not rendered as supposed and its portion of the page remains blank; 

h3. Expected Results

The presentation is reproduced correctly.
h3. Actual Results

The presentation is not reproduced. A small loading bar is spotted in the area of the presentation, but once it fills up, nothing happens.
h3. Notes
 * No error messages logged at {{atlassian-confluence.log;}}
 * Preview also doesn't work;
 * The message *unable to auto size flash - took too long to load* appears in the browser developer console when loading the page with the presentation;
 * By setting the *width* and *height* manually, the message above doesn't appear anymore, but the presentation still is not reproduced;

 
h3. Workaround

No known workarounds at this moment.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Server*. Using *Confluence Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFCLOUD-45547].
